  <static seed="1241" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions10.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{2y}{y+2}+\frac{4}{y+2}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2, y\ne -2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{2y}{y+2}+\frac{4}{y+2}} 
      \amp = \frac{{2y+4}}{{y+2}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{2\mathopen{}\left(y+2\right)}}{{y+2}} \\
      \amp = {2, y\ne -2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>y+2</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>y \ne {-2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
